Explanation:

While the documents confirm that Countess Palatine Anne Christine of Sulzbach (also known as Anne Christine or Christine of the Palatinate) was married to Charles Emmanuel of Savoy, Prince of Piedmont, they also specify that she died during childbirth in 1723. This means that she could not have been married to Charles Emmanuel III of Sardinia, who became King of Sardinia later, in 1730, and reigned until 1773.

Note: The documents do mention Charles Emmanuel III, but only as a future title held by the husband after he becomes King of Sardinia.
